                                "stop": 9.968,
                                "byte_start": 80501,
                                "byte_stop": 120416,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 94-1453, Peacock against Thomas will be announced by Justice Thomas."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.968,
                        "stop": 192.052,
                        "byte_start": 120416,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.968,
                                "stop": 20.334,
                                "byte_start": 120416,
                                "byte_stop": 161899,
                                "text": "This is a case in which the successful plaintiff is left to ask what happened to my money."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.334,
                                "stop": 42.442,
                                "byte_start": 161899,
                                "byte_stop": 250297,
                                "text": "In 1987, Jack Thomas, no relation, filed an ERISA class action in Federal Court against Tru-Tech, Inc, his former employer and D. Grant Peacock, an officer and shareholder of Tru-Tech. for the benefits due under the corporation\u0027s pension benefits plan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.442,
                                "stop": 47.172,
                                "byte_start": 250297,
                                "byte_stop": 269210,
                                "text": "He won the suit against Tru-Tech but lost against Peacock."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.172,
                                "stop": 63.423,
                                "byte_start": 269210,
                                "byte_stop": 334202,
                                "text": "Thomas did not collect the judgment while the case was on appeal and Peacock apparently settled many of Tru-Tech\u0027s accounts with favored creditors not a lease of whom was himself."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.423,
                                "stop": 88.636,
                                "byte_start": 334202,
                                "byte_stop": 435139,
                                "text": "After the appeal, Thomas was unable to collect the judgment from Tru-Tech there being no money, so he filed a new lawsuit against Peacock in Federal Court arguing among other things that the court should pierce the Corporate Veil and hold Peacock personally liable for the judgment that Thomas had won against Tru-Tech."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.636,
                                "stop": 92.971,
                                "byte_start": 435139,
                                "byte_stop": 452485,
                                "text": "The District Court agreed with Thomas and the Court of Appeals affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.971,
                                "stop": 100.21,
                                "byte_start": 452485,
                                "byte_stop": 481428,
                                "text": "We took this case decide whether the District Court had jurisdiction over Thomas\u0027 second lawsuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.21,
                                "stop": 102.333,
                                "byte_start": 481428,
                                "byte_stop": 489892,
                                "text": "We hold that it did not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.333,
                                "stop": 130.842,
                                "byte_start": 489892,
                                "byte_stop": 603890,
                                "text": "Because Thomas allege no violation of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act Codiac or of Tru-Tech\u0027s long sense terminated plan, and because the ERISA recognizes no stand along cause of action for piercing the Corporate Veil, neither ERISA\u2019s jurisdictional provision nor the general federal question statute supply the District Court with subject matter jurisdiction over the suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.842,
                                "stop": 139.825,
                                "byte_start": 603890,
                                "byte_stop": 639835,
                                "text": "We also disagree with Thomas\u2019 argument that this action is sufficiently related or ancillary to his original lawsuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.825,
                                "stop": 167.618,
                                "byte_start": 639835,
                                "byte_stop": 751012,
                                "text": "Though we have approved the exercise of ancillary jurisdiction over a broad range of supplementary proceedings involving third parties to assist in protection and enforcement of federal judgment, we have never authorized the exercise of ancillary jurisdiction in a subsequent lawsuit to transfer liability for an existing federal judgment to a person not already liable for that judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.618,
                                "stop": 176.246,
                                "byte_start": 751012,
                                "byte_stop": 785494,
                                "text": "As long as the federal rules protect the judgment creditor\u0027s ability to execute on a judgment, the District Court\u0027s authority is adequately preserved."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.246,
                                "stop": 184.19,
                                "byte_start": 785494,
                                "byte_stop": 817363,
                                "text": "An ancillary jurisdiction is not justified over a new lawsuit to impose liability for judgment on a third party."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.19,
                                "stop": 188.777,
                                "byte_start": 817363,
                                "byte_stop": 835649,
                                "text": "Accordingly, the judgment of the Court of Appeals is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 188.777,
                                "stop": 192.052,
                                "byte_start": 835649,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
